<chapter id="fixes" xreflabel="List of Fixes">

<title>Fixes Included in the Service Pack Roll</title>

<itemizedlist>

<listitem>
	<para>
	The name service (<computeroutput>named</computeroutput>) was not
	properly reloaded after a node was added with
	<computeroutput>insert-ethers</computeroutput>.
	The issue is with the configuration file
	<computeroutput>/etc/rndc.conf</computeroutput> from the 
	<computeroutput>bind</computeroutput> package found on RHEL 4
	update 3 and 4.
	</para>

	<para>
	The fix is to replace the stock 
	<computeroutput>/etc/rndc.conf</computeroutput> file with a known
	good one.
	</para>
</listitem>

<listitem>
	<para>
	On uni-processor nodes, the symbolic link to the kernel build
	environment <computeroutput>/usr/src/linux-2.6</computeroutput>
	was not properly set.
	</para>

	<para>
	This is fixed by adding the configuration script 
	<computeroutput>/etc/rc.d/rocksconfig.d/pre-10-prep-kernel-source</computeroutput>
	which runs after the buggy configuration script
	<computeroutput>/etc/rc.d/rocksconfig.d/pre-09-prep-kernel-source</computeroutput>.
	</para>
</listitem>

<listitem>
	<para>
	Fix for the <computeroutput>/tmp/sdb</computeroutput> error dialog
	which appears during installation.
	</para>

	<para>
	You no longer need to specify
	<computeroutput>nousbstorage</computeroutput> to workaround the
	problem.
	</para>
</listitem>

</itemizedlist>



</chapter>
